<FIRST>r a PM-Names Sub a0414 08-07 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Names, Sub, a0414,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS LOS ANGELES-dated 2nd item to CLARIFY that Stewart was
not boot award winner, and ADDS that Robert Mitchum won a boot.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert Duvall, star of the Emmy-nominated
miniseries ``Lonesome Dove,'' finally got the boot.
   Duvall was among 12 recipients of the Golden Boot Award,
presented Saturday by the Motion Picture and Television Fund to
actors and other entertainers who have left their brand on the
Western genre.
   In ``Lonesome Dove,'' Duvall played a former Texas Ranger who
leads a cattle drive from Texas to Montana. He also won an Oscar
for his country-western singer role in the 1983 film ``Tender
Mercies.''
   Jimmy Stewart, who did not attend the seventh annual awards
dinner, won the President Reagan Award for lifetime achievement.
   Other boot winners were Johnny Cash, Angie Dickinson, Robert
Mitchum, Casey Tibbs, Robert Fuller, Vera Miles, Paul Malvern, Dick
Jones, Ellen Corby and John Ireland also were honored. A posthumous
Boot was awarded to Andy Devine.
</TEXT>
