<FIRST>u i PM-Iran-Rafsanjani     08-07 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Iran-Rafsanjani,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rafsanjani Denies Sending Letter to Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Hashemi Rafsanjani of Iran
today denied a British newspaper report that he sent a letter to
President Bush on the hostage crisis in Lebanon.
   The Sunday Times of London reported Rafsanjani sent the letter
last week and described its tone as conciliatory.
   Rafsanjani's office today issued a statement calling the Times
report ``a bundle of lies.''
   ``Mr. Rafsanjani's stand is the same as what he mentioned in his
Friday prayer sermon in Tehran,'' the statement said.
   It was reported by the official Islamic Republic News Agency,
monitored in Cyprus.
   In his sermon Rafsanjani said the United States must pressure
Israel to release Shiek Abdul-Karim Obeid, kidnapped July 28 by
Israeli commandos in southern Lebanon.
   But he also said, ``I tell the White House, the problem of
Lebanon has solutions, the freeing of hostages has solutions,
reasonable, prudent solutions ... come let us approach the problem
reasonably. We too will help solve the problem...''
   Rafsanjani also told the United States not to resort to
``bullying and tyranny.''
</TEXT>
