<HEAD>U.S. Official, Hussein Discuss Palestinians, Hostages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMMAN, Jordan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   King Hussein conferred with a U.S. envoy
today on Palestinian rights, the Lebanese civil war and the hostage
problem, the official news agency reported.
   The Petra agency said John Kelly, U.S. assistant secretary of
state for Near Eastern affairs, delivered a letter to Hussein from
President Bush during today's two-hour meeting. It did not
elaborate.
   The agency gave no details of the talks on Lebanon and the
hostage situation.
