<HEAD>Hitler's Piano, Guillotine Stolen Before Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A piano that once belonged to Adolf
Hitler and a guillotine from the French Revolution were stolen from
a Hamburg warehouse by thieves who used a forklift, police said
today.
   The guillotine and piano were scheduled to be auctioned on Sept.
15. They were insured for $52,000 each, police said in a statement.
   Police said the thieves, operating over the weekend, used the
forklift to carry the two items to a truck.
   Hitler received the piano as a gift for his 50th birthday from
the German town of Warnsdorf.
