<FIRST>r w AM-KennedyCenterHonors     08-07 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Kennedy Center Honors,160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kennedy Center to Honor Belafonte, 4 Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Performer Harry Belafonte, actresses Claudette
Colbert and Mary Martin, dancer Alexandra Danilova and composer
William Schuman are each about to add another honor to their
scrapbooks.
   The John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts said Monday
that it will present the five artists with its annual Kennedy
Center Honors at a dinner on Dec. 2.
   The next night, the honorees will be guests of honor at a
nationally televised evening of ceremonies and performances.
Earlier that day, the award recipients will be received at the
White House by President Bush and his wife, Barbara.
   Belafonte, 62, Colbert, 85, and Martin, 75, are stars of stage,
screen and television.
   The Russian-born Danilova, 82, has been a ballerina,
choreographer, teacher and lecturer. Schuman, 79, has written 10
symphonies and numerous other works.
   The recipients were selected by the Kennedy Center's board of
trustees.
</TEXT>
