<FIRST>r i Guyana-Dog     08-07 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>Guyana-Dog,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dog On Runway Blocks Landing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GEORGETOWN, Guyana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A commercial DC-9 aircraft had to
abort a landing at Timehri international airport and then circle
the field because a dog was sunning itself on the main runway, a
newspaper reported.
   The government weekly Sunday Chronicle said the British West
Indies Airways jet was approaching for a landing Friday when the
pilot saw the dog in the center of the runway.
   The pilot scrubbed the landing and regained altitude.
   Civil Aviation Department officials scrambled aboard vehicles
and tried to shoo the dog away, but he was basking in the warmth of
the recently relaid 7,400-foot runway and balked at leaving, the
paper said.
   It took security men five minutes to scare the dog away.
Relatives and embarrassed airport staff watched as the plane
circled the airport 25 miles south of the capital.
   The plane landed safely as the dog looked for another place in
the sun.
</TEXT>
