<TEXT>
   Only a scant few still hear the muffled echos, but
this month 75 years ago, the guns of August opened the Great War
that changed the shape of the world forever.
   World War I began when a Serbian terrorist shot the archduke
expected to inherit the Austro-Hungarian empire, in a little town
named Sarajevo. Within weeks, Europe was in flames.
