<TEXT>
   The stock market retreated Friday as a stronger-than-expected
report on employment sent interest rates sharply higher.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 8.16 to
2,653.45, trimming its gain for the week to 18.21 points.
   Bond prices took their biggest spill in 22 months.
   The dollar rose nearly 2 percent against major foreign
currencies.
   Gold and silver futures prices fell sharply; the major
agricultural commodities were higher while energy futures prices
were mostly lower.
