<HEAD>Changes In Editorial Leadership at People, Money, Life</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Time Inc. announced changes Monday in the
editorial leadership at three of its magazines: People, Life and
Money.
   The changes, effective Sept. 11, were described as being part of
the periodic editorial transition at the magazines and as unrelated
to Time's recent acquisition of a controlling interest in Warner
Communications Inc.
   Patricia Ryan, the managing editor at Life since May 1987 after
five years in that position at People, will leave the company, the
announcement said. A Time spokesman said he did not know where Ryan
was going.
   She is being replaced at Life by James R. Gaines, who had been
managing editor of People.
   Landon Y. Jones, managing editor of Money magazine, replaces
Gaines as managing editor of People.
   Succeeding Jones at Money will be Frank Lalli, who had been
Money's executive editor.
